<TITLE> Journalist held in Khagrachhari on extortion charges </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Khagrachhari, Oct 24 (bdnews24.com)  Joint forces Wednesday detained the district correspondent of the Daily Samakal on charges of extortion. The arrest of Muhammad Nurul Azam, also a part-time contributor for bdnews24.com, came in the wake of a complaint filed by Khagrachhari ward commissioner Anwar Hossain. District correspondent of the Daily Ittefaq Tarun Bhattacharya told bdnews24.com by phone that following the complaint Azam was picked up from his Court Road home and taken to Khagrachhari Police Ptation. Anwar alleged that Azam ran a report in the Daily Samakal smearing him as he had not paid him the demanded extortion money. Sub-inspector Farooq Hossain said Wednesday night that Azam was being held on charges of extortion and that the police were preparing to file a case. bdnews24.co
